---
Source:
  - Title: Treasury of Traditional Wisdom
    Page: 334
Tags:
  - Combat-Action=Work, Action and Society=On ‘Karma’ and ‘Karma Yoga’
  - 197
  - 1009
Glossary:
  - Term: Namu-amida-butsu
    Definition: \‘Adoration for Amida Buddha’, an invocation used in
      the Jôdô-Shin school of Japanese Buddhism.
By: Saichi
Format: Verse
---
My birthplace? I am born of Jigoku (hell);
I am a nobody’s dog
Carrying the tail between the legs;
I pass this world of woes,
Saying ‘Namu-amida-butsu’.
